This paper proposes a method for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and specifically mentions the MSRC-21 and PASCAL VOC 2012 datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision research. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of Conditional Random Fields (CRFs), which are a type of probabilistic graphical model commonly used in machine learning, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of pre-trained models, which could suggest it belongs to cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
